Cargo.toml: version for libprosic commit:

1b6c6a298fa5f95c1ac190e76896d44065762aa9

Versions for `rust-htslib` and `rust-bio` should be set to the exact
same versions in a local checkout of libprosic set to the above commit.
This should then compile without any version troubles.

Cargo.toml: versions for libprosic commit:

59df8ce719fcbd2a9476cd01ab06feffd038b853

Versions of `rust-htslib` and `rust-bio` should be set accordingly in a
local checkout of libprosic after setting it to the above commit.
estimare.rs: adapt to newest bcf::Header API

Cargo.toml for compiling libprosic at commit:

607b3dc4f3f260e182985763385a0dbecee38e8a

Versions of `rust-htslib` and `rust-bio` need to be set exactly the
same. This is best done temporarily in a local checkout of the repo,
which is why this `Cargo.toml` lists the libprosic dependency as
`../libprosic`.

implement bulk sample min/max theor. read count

These values are used to create discrete allele frequencies to compute
probabilities for if the actual read count is below/above. However, all
reads are always used for the computation, i.e. no subsampling is taking
place.

Add starting files for simulations of testing data.

* ref.fa -- human genome GRCh38, chromosome 12, region 12022799-12023598

  the manual editing of all positions 10 + 15 * x up to and including
  position 745 for the alternative and error nucleotides in alt.fa
* alt.fa -- as ref.fa, but with manually edited sites to generate alt
  nucleotide reads
* TestSiteSimulation.ods -- positions and wanted frequencies of
  nucleotides for the two replicates of the 25 test cases as listed in
  the Events table of our manuscript
